    "narrative": "For Ghost Ride the WHIP\u2019s April 10th slate, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) represent our highest-ceiling plays. **Vinnie Pasquantino** benefits from a favorable matchup against Martin, with a significant 17% boost derived from the SP skill profile and a 14% lift from dynamic platoon positioning. **Mickey Moniak** is in an ideal spot against Walker Buehler; beyond the +19% SP skill advantage, his ability to capitalize on Buehler\u2019s slow delivery\u2014which ranks in the 90th percentile for stolen base susceptibility\u2014pairs perfectly with his #2 lineup spot, making him our primary engine for runs and swipes today. **Brice Turang** (73.40) also earns a premium start, as his leadoff role combined with an elite +19% SP skill edge against Jake Irvin makes him a high-efficiency anchor for our SB targets.\n\nThe bench decision process was tightest between **Alex Freeland** (52.45) and the rest of our utility options. While **Alex Freeland** projected reasonably well, the optimizer prioritized the higher floor and more favorable platoon splits offered by **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Seiya Suzuki**. Despite being a strong candidate, **Alex Freeland** ultimately lost out due to a projected #8 lineup position, which created a -6% drag that neutralized the benefits of the wind conditions. We are monitoring **Vinnie Pasquantino** closely, as the 31% rain risk in his matchup introduces a volatility factor that could jeopardize his efficiency if the game is significantly delayed or shortened. While **James Wood** (51.59) remains in the lineup, managers should be wary of his matchup against Aaron Ashby; despite the SB opportunity created by Ashby\u2019s slow delivery, the -19% SP skill penalty against the lefty keeps his score near the marginal threshold.",
